courses.learning_outcomes:
The primary objective of this course is to provide an introduction to financial concepts and fundamental principles for undergraduate business students who have little prior knowledge or training in finance. It is intended to be basic. At the end of the semester, students are expected to be able to:
~ improve their understanding of the vocabulary of finance;
~ communicate more effectively with financial practitioners;
~ develop guidelines to assess the performance of a firm in financial terms;
~ enhance their ability to use financial analysis when required to make decisions;
~ better understand the impact of financial decisions on the performance of a firm;
~ develop a critical thinking mindset.

