To provide students with the theoretical backgrounds necessary to appreciate and understand problems faced by financial managers in an international setting.

(1) To discuss current developments in the international financial arena;
(2) To understand the basics of international financial environments;
(3) To examine the use of international financial markets to control risk and maximise firm value; and
(4) To apply and integrate relevant concepts through written essays.

The primary objective of this course is to provide an introduction to the theories and practices of trading strategies commonly used by investment banks and hedged funds. At the end of the course, students are expected to be able to:
- understand basic trading techniques of warrants/CBBCs;
- understand the profit sources of trading warrants/CBBCs by issuers and the risk/difficulties involved;
- calculate the portfolio used in index arbitrage and Hang Seng Index rebalancing trades;
- understand the concept of risk cycling and volatility arbitrage between structured products, listed options and warrants;
- understand the concept of premium/discount arbitrage of ETFs and Tracker Funds.

The primary objective of this course is to provide an introduction to the theories and practices in security analysis. At the end of the course, students are expected to be able to:

~ predict the effect of government policies on key macroeconomic variables;
~ analyze the effect of industry life cycles and structures on industry earnings prospects over time;
~ calculate the intrinsic value of a stock using various techniques and models;
~ assess the growth prospect of a firm from its price-earnings ratio;
~ value a firm using free cash flow models and the concept of terminal value;
~ identify the determinants of bond safety and rating.

courses.course_syllabus:
Topics include:
(1) Commonly used severity and frequency distributions and their properties;
(2) Statistical estimation and tests of parametric severity and frequency distributions;
(3) Computation of aggregate loss distribution, including convolution, generating function, recursive calculation, and lognormal and mixture of Gamma approximation, impact of coverage modifications, stop-loss premium;
(4) Credibility theory, including the Bayesian methodology, classical credibility and greatest accuracy credibility model.

內容包括：
(1) 常用頻率與損失分佈及特性
(2) 頻率與損失分佈之估計與統計檢定
(3) 整體損失模型的運算, 包括旋積、產 生函數、遞迴、對數正態和伽瑪之混合分佈之概算、保險責任調整之影響、停止損失保費
(4) 可信度理論，包括貝葉氏分析、經典可信度與最準確度可信度模型

Topics include:
(1) Discrete- and continuous Markov chain model to model cash flows for life and health insurance policies;
(2) Estimation of transition probabilities and intensities of Markov chain;
(3) Run-off triangle for estimating reserves for unpaid losses for general insurance;
(4) Calculate premiums for general insurance using the pure premium and loss ratio methods.

內容包括：
(1) 離時與連時馬爾可夫鏈模擬人壽保險和醫療保險的現金流
